events_joined.description:
Mull :   mÊl/
verb: mull; 3rd person present: mulls; past tense: mulled; past participle: mulled; gerund or present participle: mulling

1. Think about (something) deeply and at length
2. Warm (an alcoholic drink, especially wine or beer) and add sugar and spices to it.
"an ocean of mulled wine, drunk with friends"

Something has been missing from our lives, and after thinking about it deeply and at length, we've decided that it is a party based around a warm alcoholic drink with added sugar and spices. Spicy, sweet, warm friendship, warding off the cold dark night with hot wine and wit. We promise to not play Christmas music until midnight. After, we make no promises.

Bring Your Own Mug (and drinks)! Unfortunately, we are not made of money, nor are we made of mugs, so make sure you bring a mug, or prepare to drink mulled wine out of a leftover Halloween bucket. Bring some wine pre-mulled, or some to add to the cauldron (however much mulled wine you want), and whatever else you want to drink. The only alcohol supplied will be a little mulled wine, at least until late.

Don't Wear White! I mean this is optional, but it's literally a party where the main drink is hot wine, this just seems obvious. Unless you want to leave the party looking like you've just got a shit halloween costume, avoid expensive white clothing.

We'll be mulling and drinking from latest 18.00 onwards, because it feels like mulled wine drinking should be begun earlyish, roughly aprÃ©s-ski time. Join us whenever., the sooner the bettter

It's not a big flat, and it's probably going to be full so plus ones are going to be hard. Limited smoking space, only one toilet, no party poopers...

events_joined.description:
I figured we should all get together for an evening before we all break up for Christmas. My halls has a bar that serves Â£1 Budweisers, Â£1.50 Coronas and Â£2.50 Vodka mixers. We also have a table tennis table (did I hear someone say beer pong?), table football and a pool table too. Also if we do it here I don't have to move. 

As I'm sure (I hope) you are all aware, the fantastic (free) Friday night institution of ULU is just round the corner from University, and conveniently, so is my halls, so I figured we could all come here for drinks from 8-11pm (when the bar closes), and then those who wanted to come to ULU could then do so.

Because the bar is properly licensed and stuff, you can't drink your own drinks in the bar area until it closes at 11, but if you want to save some money (i.e. Â£1 a beer was too steep for your budget), then feel free to bring a few bits for post bar and pre-ULU from 11.00-11.30.

Looking forward to seeing you all there, let me know soon-ish if you can come so I can tell the bar manager how many bar staff will be needed!
